eldyvoon:
It's annoying the dist directory which in ur case is img/src, I solved that by altering the value of replace.js
```
...
patterns: [
        {
          match: /(<img[^>]+[\"'])(\.\.\/src\/img\/)/gi,  // Matches <img * src="../src/img or <img * src='../src/img'
          replacement: '$1../'
        },
        {
          match: /(url\(*[^)])(\.\.\/src\/img\/)/gi,  // Matches url('../src/img') or url(../src/img) and even url("../src/img")
          replacement: '$1../'
        }
      ]
...
